Vice President Biden met with South African Deputy President Motlanthe to discuss the deepening and expanding relations between the United States and South Africa. They talked about various ways in which the two countries will work together to advance shared goals in development, security, and economic interests. They highlighted the importance of the U.S.-South Africa Strategic Dialogue, which covers issues like health, education, agriculture, trade, energy, and regional security. The Vice President praised South Africa's efforts in the fight against HIV/AIDS and emphasized the need to sustain these achievements. They also discussed the situations in Zimbabwe and Sudan, as well as global initiatives such as nuclear non-proliferation, climate change, and food security.